<li id="cite_note-119"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-119">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See the development, by generations of mathematicians, of <a href="/wiki/Euler%27s_formula_for_polyhedra" class="mw-redirect" title="Euler's formula for polyhedra">Euler's formula for polyhedra</a> as documented by <cite id="CITEREFLakatos1976" class="citation"><a href="/wiki/Imre_Lakatos" title="Imre Lakatos">Lakatos, Imre</a> (1976), <i><a href="/wiki/Proofs_and_refutations" class="mw-redirect" title="Proofs and refutations">Proofs and refutations</a></i>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-521-29038-4" title="Special:BookSources/0-521-29038-4">0-521-29038-4</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Proofs+and+refutations&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1976&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-29038-4&amp;rft.aulast=Lakatos&amp;rft.aufirst=Imre&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AScientific+method" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
